com.guimonsters.client

Class GameCommands

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.guimonsters.client.GameCommands
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    LoggedInCommands, LoggedOutCommands, PlayingCommands

    public class GameCommands
extends java.lang.Object
    Master Class for Commands available to specific states of gameplay. Collects and handles parsing and event dispatching for all game commands.
    Version:
    1.00, 2013-04-18
    Author:
    Elijah Atkinson, Stephen Butler, Curran Hamilton

    • Constructor Detail

      • GameCommands

        public GameCommands(MudClient client)
        Create a GameCommands instance that can be used to parse user input and dispatch the appropriate event. GameCommands assumes user input has been previously sanitized.
        Parameters:
        client - The master game client object used by commands.

    • Method Detail

      • parseCommand

        public java.lang.String parseCommand(java.lang.String c)
        Check the command HashMap for the command string matching user input. If found, execute the function mapped to the input string and return the result.
        Parameters:
        c - The String input to attempt to parse and execute.
        Returns:
        results The String returned by the function mapped to the given input string. Results is null if no function was found for the input string or if the function failed to execute.

      • printHelp

        public java.lang.String printHelp()
        Responds to the user command 'help'. Iterate through the HashMap of game commands and print description field of every game command.
        Returns:
        helpStr The String containing the help message.

      • clearGameLog

        public void clearGameLog()
        Responds to the user command 'clear'. Clears the main Game Log. Adds the prompt for the current state to the gameLog.

      • logOut

        public void logOut()
        Logs the user out of the game and returns to the LOGGED_OUT state.

      • prompt

        public void prompt()
        Print the default prompt for the current game state to the game log.
